         PPG Industries Inc Careers & Jobs 








PPG Industries Inc Company Information


PPG Industries Inc. OverviewPPG Industries Inc. is a global supplier of coatings and specialty products. Their line includes paints, glass, fiberglass, and optical products, as well as specialty materials. PPG has customers in several markets including construction, industrial, transportation, and consumer products. With total net sales of $15.4 billion in 2014, PPG ranks at 190 in the Fortune 500.PPG is a leading innovator in the industry with standout products that include aircraft coatings with corrosion protection and a lighter weight for better fuel efficiency; carefully color-matched, eco-friendly automotive coatings; and antifouling solutions for marine equipment. PPG coatings are used on everything from lightweight wind turbines for renewable energy to high performance coatings for beverage cans.PPG Industries Inc. Job OpportunitiesPPG Industries employs over 46,000 people worldwide, including more than 18,000 in North America; 14,000 in Europe, the Middle East, and Africa; nearly 6,000 in Latin America; and over 7,000 in the Asia Pacific. The headquarters for PPG Industries Inc are based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania.PPG looks for employees with an outstanding dedication to innovation and success. The company typically has job openings for applicants at nearly any experience level, from retail sales associates to product stewardship specialists. Graphic designers, production managers, customer relations representatives, and sales analysts all hold important roles throughout the product's journey.PPG Industries Inc. Work CulturePPG maintains an internal job-posting program that promotes in-house advancement. The company encourages continuing education in both formal and informal environments and facilitates mentoring and networking relationships. Fitness centers and wellness programs promote employee health while opportunities for telecommuting and flexible work hours support a manageable work-life balance.PPG Industries prides itself on its commitment to sustainability, both in its products and in its workplace. Around the world, the company has implemented innovative solutions, such as introducing sheep to the Eco Pasture at the Ruitz, France site, which will eliminate the need for lawn maintenance and reduce soil degradation.

View More





